response: Following his release from Cambridge, Carr rejoined Dulwich Hamlet ahead of the 2016–17 season. On 13 August 2016, Carr made his Dulwich Hamlet return in a 2–2 draw against AFC Sudbury, playing 74 minutes before being replaced by Victor Adeboyejo. On 16 August 2016, Carr scored his first goal for Dulwich Hamlet since his spell in the 2012–13 campaign, in a 2–1 victory over Enfield Town.
